---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Next.js Directory Website Development | Stackbase System" description="Next.js directory website development for dynamic features, authentication, and scalable product workflows.">
  <section class="pt-24 pb-14">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <span class="text-sm text-[#00f0ff] font-['JetBrains_Mono'] tracking-wider">NEXT.JS DIRECTORY BUILD</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mt-4 mb-5 font-['Space_Grotesk']">Next.js directory website development for dynamic product features</h1>
      <p class="text-[#8b8b9a] text-lg max-w-3xl">When your directory needs authentication, user-generated actions, and backend workflows, Next.js gives you product flexibility while still allowing strong SEO architecture and performance discipline.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-8">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-xs text-[#8b8b9a]">Best Fit</p><p class="text-white mt-1">Feature-rich directories</p></div>
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-xs text-[#8b8b9a]">Common Need</p><p class="text-white mt-1">Auth + ownership workflows</p></div>
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl p-5"><p class="text-xs text-[#8b8b9a]">Delivery Style</p><p class="text-white mt-1">Core build + scoped add-ons</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-10">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-white font-['Space_Grotesk'] mb-4">Typical Next.js directory features</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-[#c7c7d2]">
          <li>• Login/signup and permission-based areas</li>
          <li>• Listing claim workflows and owner dashboards</li>
          <li>• User submissions, moderation, and activity states</li>
          <li>• Dynamic APIs for search, updates, and workflows</li>
          <li>• Scalable architecture for post-launch product expansion</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-2xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl text-white font-['Space_Grotesk'] mb-4">How scope stays safe</h2>
        <p class="text-[#8b8b9a]">Feature-heavy projects can spiral quickly. Stackbase keeps delivery practical: core architecture first, then modular add-ons (auth, role systems, custom tools) so budget and timeline remain predictable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-10">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="bg-[#151520] border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl text-white font-['Space_Grotesk'] mb-4">When to choose Next.js over Astro</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-[#c7c7d2]">
          <p>• You need account systems and personalized experiences</p>
          <p>• You need ongoing backend interactions and logic-heavy workflows</p>
          <p>• You expect rapid feature iteration after launch</p>
          <p>• You want one platform for both directory SEO and app features</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-14">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-[#0a0a0f] bg-gradient-to-r from-[#00f0ff] to-[#00c8ff] rounded-xl">See packages + add-ons</a>
      <a href="/astro-directory-website-development" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl">Compare with Astro path</a>
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white border border-[#2a2a3a] rounded-xl">Send feature requirements</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
